  "_doc": "Phase-5e demo (part 2): CU and BUS — the two more involved CPU pieces. Click VERILOG to see the canonical patterns:\n  • CU (Control Unit) — pure combinational decoder over a 4-bit OP, built as one nested-ternary chain per output. Six control outputs (ALU_OP, RG_WE, MM_WE, MM_RE, JMP, HALT, IMM) drive the rest of the datapath. JMP gates on Z (BEQ → `z`) or ~Z (BNE → `~z`). Default 16-op ISA is hardcoded; node.controlTable lets you override.\n  • BUS — multi-driver bus, lowered to a priority-MUX (en0 > en1 > en2 > 1'bz). No internal multi-driver tri-state; one continuous assign on the bus net. ERR output flags multi-active conflicts via zero-extended population count. This is the lowerTriState pass the README plan called for at Phase 5.",
